    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>A stone figure, humanoid, carved in ancient Keeper craftsmanship. Created to defend the archive from intrusion. Half-corrupted by the Rot — part of its stone face is blackened and cracking. It does not attack immediately, but bars the way, watching. It senses Kaelen’s ember-mark and can be persuaded to stand aside.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>ABILITIES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Stone Fist</strong> (Main, Melee, Might): T1 2 dmg; T2 5 dmg; T3 7 dmg.</li><li><strong>Keeper’s Judgment</strong> (Main, Area 30ft, Presence): T1 1 dmg + pushed 2; T2 3 dmg + pushed 5; T3 5 dmg + pushed 10.</li></ul><p><strong>FEATURES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Stone Form:</strong> Immune to poison and disease. Resist non-magical damage.</li><li><strong>Decay:</strong> When damaged, roll d6. On 6: the construct loses its next action.</li><li><strong>Threshold Guardian:</strong> Does not pursue beyond the boundary of its guarded area.</li><li><strong>Recognition:</strong> Recognizes Kaelen as a Keeper (ember-mark). If she introduces herself as Keeper, the construct may stand aside without combat (Presence TN 13).</li></ul><p>Beat 15, Ivory Tower. Optional/atmospheric encounter. ES ~8. Half-corrupted by Rot (part of stone face blackened).</p>",
